<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Prepare Your Computer for Gaming Use</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1003" relname="preparation">Welcome to a brief tutorial</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1004" relname="background">on how to squeeze every last bit of performance out of your computer , for gaming .</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="1005" relname="span">This is going to be strictly software</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="4" relname="elaboration">based</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1007" relname="span">and will show you ways</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="6" relname="purpose">to fine tune your system</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="1008" relname="span">to get slight performance increases</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="8" relname="manner">without having to buy new hardware .</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="1010" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1010" relname="sequence">Now the first thing</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1014" relname="span">I always like to do</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="12" relname="circumstance">when I get my hands on a new system ,</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1013" relname="same_unit">is to do a clean install of whichever Windows system is newest .</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="1016" relname="span">So in this case I would make a bootable flash drive</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1017" relname="joint">using the official Windows 10 ISO ,</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="1018" relname="span">and placing it onto a flash drive</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="17" relname="means">using the Rufus application .</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="1021" relname="condition">Now after the system has had a clean install ,</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="1021" relname="span">with no bloatware or other pre-loaded junk</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="20" relname="elaboration">that hardware manufactuers love to load onto our systems .</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="1023" relname="span">It &apos;s always a good idea</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="22" relname="purpose">to run the disk cleanup , as well as defrag and optimize the disk .</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="1023" relname="justify">These programs can be found and launched in the &quot; Windows administrative tools &quot; folder .</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1025" relname="span">Now you can access what we need in this next step</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="1026" relname="sequence">by clicking on the little batter icon on the far right side of the Windows taskbar ,</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1026" relname="sequence">and select &quot; more power options &quot; .</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="1027" relname="span">This should take you to a control panel window with options for &quot; powersaver mode &quot; and &quot; balanced mode &quot; , as well as a hidden third option .</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="1029" relname="span">To get to this hidden option</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="29" relname="elaboration">you will need to click the little dropdown icon on the far right of the window .</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1031" relname="span">You &apos;ll see an option come down</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="31" relname="elaboration">called &quot; High performance mode &quot; .</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1033" relname="span">Which will typically keep restrictions on your processor state off regardless of the battery life</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="33" relname="elaboration">( assuming you have a laptop ) .</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="1035" relname="sequence">Next up you want to access your control panel</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="1035" relname="sequence">and go to System and Security &gt; System &gt; Advanced System Settings in the far left toolbar .</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="1037" relname="joint">This will open up a new , smaller window for system properties .</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="1038" relname="joint">Click the settings button under performance</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="1039" relname="span">and click the circle choice for &quot; Adjust for best performance &quot; ,</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="1040" relname="span">apply and click &quot; OK &quot;</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="40" relname="purpose">to exit the window .</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="1041" relname="joint">Next thing is the most important .</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="1043" relname="preparation">Find out what graphics card you have .</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="1044" relname="span">It &apos;ll let you know where to go</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="1045" relname="span">in order to get updates for the graphics card driver ,</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="45" relname="elaboration">which will help your system better take advantage of your video card &apos;s resources .</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="1049" relname="condition">If you &apos;re really scrimping for system memory</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1049" relname="span">then I would suggest downloading Razer Cortex</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="48" relname="elaboration">( formally known as game booster ) .</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="1050" relname="joint">It not only can dynamically shut down processes</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1052" relname="circumstance">when a game launches ,</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="1052" relname="span">but it also has some great tweak tools</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="1053" relname="span">to adjust system settings</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1054" relname="span">that are generally harder to find ,</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="54" relname="elaboration">which can lead to some more performance increases .</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1056" relname="span">Now , some more steps</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="1057" relname="same_unit">to take</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="1058" relname="joint">are to clean up your system</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="1058" relname="joint">and just generally do some housekeeping work on it from time to time .</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="1060" relname="span">Keep as few items on the desktop</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="1062" relname="span">as possible</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="61" relname="elaboration">( I typically only keep the recycle bin icon on my desktop ) ,</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="1063" relname="span">clean out your downloads folder</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="1064" relname="joint">whenever you can ,</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="1065" relname="same_unit">and organize any files</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="1065" relname="same_unit">you use constantly .</segment>
<segment id="67" parent="1066" relname="joint">Running the defrag tools periodically wo n&apos;t hurt either .</segment>
<segment id="68" parent="1068" relname="preparation">Make sure ALL of your drivers are up to date .</segment>
<segment id="69" parent="1070" relname="attribution">You never understand</segment>
<segment id="70" parent="1070" relname="span">how important an updated Wifi driver is</segment>
<segment id="71" parent="70" relname="circumstance">until you experience lag spikes and performance issues with any kind of online game .</segment>
<segment id="72" parent="1071" relname="joint">Make sure you know what is running in the background at all times .</segment>
<segment id="73" parent="1073" relname="joint">Not only is it a good rule of thumb ,</segment>
<segment id="74" parent="1074" relname="span">but also , I ca n&apos;t tell you how many times I &apos;ve had to quit or alt+tab out of a game</segment>
<segment id="75" parent="1075" relname="span">to turn off Google Chrome</segment>
<segment id="76" parent="75" relname="circumstance">when it was running in the background .</segment>
<segment id="77" parent="1076" relname="joint">Finally , restart your computer every now and then .</segment>
<segment id="78" parent="1077" relname="joint">Do n&apos;t just leave the thing going on for days , even weeks on end .</segment>
<segment id="79" parent="1078" relname="joint">I &apos;d say at least once a day just run a restart ,</segment>
<segment id="80" parent="1079" relname="joint">it &apos;ll let the system dump some loose data</segment>
<segment id="81" parent="1079" relname="joint">and get a fresh start .</segment>
